Certainly! Here is an example of output from the National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST) without a CPE query:


https://services.nvd.nist.gov/rest//cves/2.0?startIndex=0&resultsPerPage=XXXX
{
"resultsPerPage": XXXX,
"startIndex": 0,
"totalResults": 240564,
"format": "NVD_CVE",
"version": "2.0",
"timestamp": "2024-03-05T15:08:36.657",
"vulnerabilities": [
{"cve": {"id": "CVE-1999-0095", ... }}
{"cve": {"id": "CVE-1999-0082", ... }}
... total of XXXX results â€¦
]
}

This response structure provides information about vulnerabilities, with each entry having a CVE ID such as CVE-1999-0095 and CVE-1999-0082.
